  "prompt": "How do I stop a German Shepherd/Border Collie mix puppy from chewing my shoes?",
  "response": "Here are several strategies to prevent your puppy from chewing shoes:\n\n1. Preventative Measures\n- Keep shoes out of reach\n- Use baby gates or crates when you can't supervise\n- Put shoes in closed closets or high shelves\n\n2. Provide Appropriate Chew Alternatives\n- Get plenty of chew toys\n- Offer different textures and sizes of chew toys\n- Use puzzle toys to keep them mentally stimulated\n- Rotate toys to maintain interest\n\n3. Training Techniques\n- Use positive reinforcement when they chew appropriate toys\n- Say \"No\" firmly if caught chewing shoes\n- Redirect to appropriate chew toys immediately\n- Never punish after the fact\n- Use bitter spray on shoes as a deterrent\n\n4. Exercise and Mental Stimulation\n- Ensure plenty of daily exercise\n- Provide mental stimulation through training\n- Border Collie/German Shepherd mixes are high-energy breeds\n- Tired dogs are less likely to chew destructively\n\n5. Teething Management\n- Provide frozen washcloths or teething toys\n- Be patient during teething phase (typically 3-6 months)\n\nConsistency is key in preventing unwanted chewing behavior.",
